<br>
Peleus turned to those assembled, &quot;I am thankful this day to be married to this wonderful Goddess, and look forward to many days with her by my side.&quot;<br>
<br>
With a clap of his hands, suddenly servents flowed forth bringing in more large platters of food and wine sprung forth from marble fountains, &quot;My friends, join me in a celebration of food, wine, and love, &quot;exclaimed Peleus as he then took his wife's hand and lead her over to a table to sup. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/21/01 7:37:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/qherarpg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arrives</span><hr size=1> Hera quietly watched as her husband arrived.  She was a bit perturbed with him, as she knew very well where he most likely was.  Deciding not to give him the warm greeting he received from his beloved daughter, Athena....Hera turned her steely gaze back to the couple.<br>
<br>
Not wanting to make a noise as the ceremony had suddenly began, Hera nodded to Nike and gave her a slight smile.  Then again turning her icy blue eyes to the couple as they were joined.  <br>
<br>
The ceremony was beautiful she thought.  As Peleus invited all the guests to enjoy the feast, Hera stood there still, a bit irratated at her husband.  Her jealousy had been boiling into a rare form lately, as she had not seen her husband in sometime.  And seeing the happy couple, did not help. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/21/01 7:51:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arrives</span><hr size=1> ::A dark mist disperses after Poseidon arrives in the midst of the ceremony on Mount Pelion with his gifts. He has two immortal horses with him and holds their reigns in his hand. In his other hand he has a parchment congradulating the couple in their marriage, sealed by a golden shell-shaped seal. He has on a silk toga with gold outlining. It is held up wth golden pins. On his feet are a pair of golden sandles and on top of his wavy brown hair is his golden crown. He sees a table being set with food and drink and some of his fellow Olympians and immortals there. Poseidon walks up to the table where the meal is being served guiding the horses along.:: <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A> at: 10/21/01 7:53:55 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uaubard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AU Bard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazons Unite Bard</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font col